WEBVTT

01:00.934 --> 01:04.937
628 Tremont. 6-2-8. Three dead.

01:04.938 --> 01:07.773
No, just the usual. Fuck. Usual.

01:07.774 --> 01:09.567
It's no big deal these days, right?

01:09.568 --> 01:11.235
- Some guy-- What's his name?
- I don't know.

01:11.236 --> 01:13.946
Oh, who knows his name?
Who cares?

01:13.947 --> 01:17.950
Fucking' shoots his wife and kid,
and then eats the fucking licorice.

01:17.951 --> 01:20.786
Sticks it in his mouth
and blows his own brains out.

01:22.164 --> 01:23.956
- This guy had no ID--
- Shit.

01:23.957 --> 01:26.042
...no fucking papers.

01:26.043 --> 01:28.294
Probably squirreled
over the goddamn border.

01:28.295 --> 01:30.171
Hey, guys. Channel 10 News.

01:30.172 --> 01:31.964
Listen, you're kind of blocking our shot.

01:31.965 --> 01:33.591
- Can I get you to move forward a bit?
- Yeah, sure.

01:33.592 --> 01:35.051
Thanks. You ready?

01:35.052 --> 01:37.220
Yeah. Almost. Two minutes.

01:37.221 --> 01:40.306
Let's grab some more B-roll.

01:40.307 --> 01:42.225
Can't get close enough for an Emmy.

01:42.226 --> 01:44.602
Screw the Emmy.
I'd settle for a fucking paycheck.

01:44.603 --> 01:45.978
Story of my life.

01:45.979 --> 01:47.980
We downloaded this video off the Net

01:47.981 --> 01:49.982
sometime over the last three days.

01:49.983 --> 01:51.776
I can't remember exactly when.

01:51.777 --> 01:53.194
Look at this guy.

01:53.195 --> 01:55.321
Look at this fucking guy.

01:55.322 --> 01:58.157
Chowing down while his buddies are
shoving a corpse in the back of the van.

01:58.158 --> 01:59.992
- Okay, I'm ready. Let's do it.
- Some of this footage

01:59.993 --> 02:01.702
- was never broadcast.
- Am I good?

02:01.703 --> 02:04.497
It was secretly uploaded
by the cameraman who shot it.

02:04.498 --> 02:06.540
- It was his way of trying to--
- She's alive.

02:06.541 --> 02:09.001
...tell the truth
about what was happening.

02:09.002 --> 02:11.212
Bree Reno reporting live from Homestead,

02:11.213 --> 02:14.006
where tragedy befell
an immigrant family.

02:14.007 --> 02:15.591
An unidentified man has shot

02:15.592 --> 02:18.469
his wife and 16-year-old son
to death

02:18.470 --> 02:21.514
- before turning the gun on himself.
- Hey, what's going on?

02:21.515 --> 02:23.432
- Jesus!
- What?

02:23.433 --> 02:24.558
- I don't believe this.
- What?

02:24.559 --> 02:25.810
Is there something with the camera?

02:25.811 --> 02:28.020
- Just fix it.
- She's still moving.

02:28.021 --> 02:30.523
Oh, for Christ's sake, Brody.
I'm right in the middle of a--

02:30.524 --> 02:32.817
- What?
- Jesus-fucking-Christ!

02:32.818 --> 02:35.027
- For God's sakes!
- What the hell is going on over there?

02:35.028 --> 02:37.697
- I thought they were dead.
- They're supposed to be. They are--

02:37.698 --> 02:40.491
I don't know! She's moving
on the frickin' gurney, man!

02:40.492 --> 02:42.326
Get out of the way!
Come on! Get out of the way!

02:42.327 --> 02:45.663
Backup here! Backup here!

02:45.664 --> 02:48.040
- Aah!
- Get off of him!

02:48.041 --> 02:49.750
He all right?

02:49.751 --> 02:52.420
Jesus! What the fuck is that?

02:52.421 --> 02:54.046
Just keep still.

02:54.047 --> 02:58.175
The other one's moving!

02:59.177 --> 03:01.929
The other one's coming up, too!

03:01.930 --> 03:05.057
No!

03:05.058 --> 03:10.058
- Take him out!

03:11.315 --> 03:13.816
He's not going down!

03:13.817 --> 03:16.819
He's not going down!

03:17.821 --> 03:20.948
Holy shit!

03:20.949 --> 03:22.950
Bree!

03:22.951 --> 03:27.079
- Shoot her in the head!

03:27.080 --> 03:29.373
No. No.

03:29.374 --> 03:31.083
This can't be happening.

03:31.084 --> 03:33.085
This can't be fucking happening!

03:36.965 --> 03:38.549
We downloaded
a lot of what we found

03:38.550 --> 03:41.177
on television, on the Net, off blogs--

03:41.178 --> 03:44.388
images and commentary
over those first three days.

03:44.389 --> 03:46.182
Most of it was bullshit.

03:46.183 --> 03:47.975
None of it was useful.

03:47.976 --> 03:50.603
This is what we were getting
from the news networks.

03:50.604 --> 03:52.355
None of us can claim to know

03:52.356 --> 03:55.024
exactly what has caused the chaos
we've been experiencing.

03:55.025 --> 03:56.233
Some kind of germ.
Some kind of epidemic.

03:56.234 --> 03:57.360
A natural calamity or--

03:57.361 --> 03:59.278
You can't talk about it
being an epidemic.

03:59.279 --> 04:01.572
You talk about it being an epidemic,
there's gonna be panic in the streets.

04:01.573 --> 04:03.991
I'm old enough to remember
Orson Welles' War of the Worlds,

04:03.992 --> 04:06.369
possibly the greatest hoax
every perpetrated.

04:06.370 --> 04:08.329
- There's a dead guy sitting up!
- And that was when it was just radio.

04:08.330 --> 04:10.206
Now it's 24/7.

04:10.207 --> 04:11.290
This is some kind of hoax.

04:13.543 --> 04:15.544
This is ridiculous!

04:15.545 --> 04:18.505
People are
willing to believe almost anything.

04:18.507 --> 04:20.048
We made a film--

04:20.050 --> 04:22.051
the one I'm going to show you now.

04:22.052 --> 04:26.389
Actually, Jason was the one
who wanted to make it.

04:26.390 --> 04:29.016
Like that cameraman from Channel 10,

04:29.017 --> 04:32.228
he wanted to upload it
so that people-- you--

04:32.229 --> 04:34.230
could be told the truth.

04:34.231 --> 04:37.733
The film was shot
with a Panasonic HDX-900

04:37.734 --> 04:39.693
and an HBX-200.

04:39.694 --> 04:42.738
I did the final cut on Jason's laptop.

04:42.739 --> 04:47.618
I've added music occasionally
for effect, hoping to scare you.

04:47.619 --> 04:50.329
You see, in addition to trying
to tell you the truth,

04:50.330 --> 04:52.706
I am hoping to scare you

04:52.707 --> 04:56.419
so that maybe you'll wake up.

04:56.420 --> 05:00.256
Maybe you won't make any of
the same mistakes that we made.

05:00.257 --> 05:03.926
Anyway, here it is, Jason Creed's

05:03.927 --> 05:08.927
The Death of Death.

05:29.202 --> 05:34.202
- Aah!

05:35.167 --> 05:37.042
No. Cut, cut.

05:37.043 --> 05:39.128
- Cut.
- Come on!

05:39.129 --> 05:41.005
How many times have I told you?

05:41.006 --> 05:43.007
Dead things don't move fast.

05:43.008 --> 05:44.508
You're a corpse, for Christ's sakes.

05:44.509 --> 05:47.136
If you run that fast,
your ankles are gonna snap off.

05:47.137 --> 05:48.971
If she's going fast, I have to go fast,

05:48.972 --> 05:50.681
otherwise, how
am I supposed to catch her?

05:50.682 --> 05:53.100
You're supposed to catch her later.

05:53.101 --> 05:54.810
This is the beginning
of the fucking movie.

05:54.811 --> 05:56.812
You catch her now, it's all over.

05:56.813 --> 05:59.690
All you're supposed to do
is grab her dress so--

05:59.691 --> 06:02.610
So my tits fall out?
Ain't gonna happen.

06:02.611 --> 06:04.320
You know, can somebody
please explain to me

06:04.321 --> 06:07.156
why girls in scary movies
always have to, like,

06:07.157 --> 06:09.658
fall down and lose
their shoes and shit?

06:09.659 --> 06:12.328
It's totally lame.

06:12.329 --> 06:14.330
And why do we always have
to get our dresses torn off?

06:14.331 --> 06:16.123
Actually, I'm looking forward to that part.

06:16.124 --> 06:18.125
- Flashing.
- I swear.

06:18.126 --> 06:20.252
- Thanks.
- Should've stuck with auto repair.

06:20.253 --> 06:23.088
Aw, shit, man. Look at this.
Your makeup's all unglued.

06:23.089 --> 06:25.424
Give me a break.

06:25.425 --> 06:28.135
Yeah, maybe you can see it now
because you're in way too tight.

06:28.136 --> 06:29.887
All he's supposed to do
is run through the fucking shot.

06:29.888 --> 06:32.556
No, not run. Shamble.

06:32.557 --> 06:35.726
The script says, "The mummy
shambles into frame and stops."

06:35.727 --> 06:37.895
For a second. For one second.

06:37.896 --> 06:39.563
You're telling me
in one second you can see--

06:39.564 --> 06:40.689
The camera can see.

06:40.690 --> 06:43.234
And what the camera sees,
the audience will see.

06:43.235 --> 06:44.527
What fucking audience?

06:44.528 --> 06:47.404
There's always an audience for horror--
believable horror.

06:47.405 --> 06:50.533
But who's gonna believe a mummy
if his makeup's all unglued?

06:50.534 --> 06:53.035
Who's gonna believe
a mummy in the first place?

06:53.036 --> 06:55.204
Here's a thought, genius--
try zooming out.

06:55.205 --> 06:56.664
Maybe your fucking shot will work.

06:56.665 --> 06:59.124
I know what I want here, Tony,
and I know what I'm doing.

06:59.125 --> 07:00.918
That's right. You do, don't you?

07:00.919 --> 07:04.672
We're only, what, four days over
a three-day shooting schedule?

07:04.673 --> 07:06.674
Guys, there's something weird going on.

07:06.675 --> 07:09.134
Don't even get fucking credits
for what we're doing out here.

07:09.135 --> 07:11.178
You'll all be in the credits.

07:11.179 --> 07:12.680
I'm talking about college credits.

07:12.681 --> 07:15.307
Leave those to me.

07:15.308 --> 07:17.101
Did we get the shot yet?

07:17.102 --> 07:18.686
No, we're still clicking around.

07:18.687 --> 07:23.566
Five credits for each of you.
That is a pledge.

07:23.567 --> 07:26.318
Mr. Creed has a vision.

07:26.319 --> 07:28.487
Hey, I'm just trying to make
a scary movie here.

07:28.488 --> 07:29.613
Yes, you are, Mr. Creed.

07:29.614 --> 07:30.781
Jason always wanted to be

07:30.782 --> 07:32.825
a documentary filmmaker.

07:32.826 --> 07:34.702
But for his senior class project,

07:34.703 --> 07:37.705
he decided to try to make a horror film.

07:37.706 --> 07:41.041
That's what he was shooting
on that first night,

07:41.042 --> 07:44.712
the night when... everything changed.

07:44.713 --> 07:46.422
Stupid fucking mummy movie.

07:46.423 --> 07:49.466
With an underlying thread
of social satire.

07:49.467 --> 07:52.720
Jason, can I take a minute?
I have to pee.

07:52.721 --> 07:54.638
- Shit!
- Uh, Jason?

07:54.639 --> 07:56.765
- What?
- I have to pee, too.

07:56.766 --> 07:58.183
Jesus Christ!

07:58.184 --> 07:59.977
This whole thing is falling apart.

08:01.438 --> 08:02.730
There's something on the news.

08:02.731 --> 08:05.733
It's pretty-- Well, I mean...

08:05.734 --> 08:07.735
you might wanna check this out.

08:07.736 --> 08:10.195
It's difficult for us
to believe what we've been reporting,

08:10.196 --> 08:11.739
but it does seem to be happening.

08:11.740 --> 08:15.659
Two news agencies in two separate
counties in the Tri-State area

08:15.660 --> 08:19.455
are reporting accounts
of the dead returning to life.

08:19.456 --> 08:21.749
In one of the cases--
the one in Somerset--

08:21.750 --> 08:25.753
the dead man, identified
as a 50-year-old white male,

08:25.754 --> 08:28.631
the victim of
a drive-by shooting yesterday,

08:28.632 --> 08:31.759
sat up on an autopsy table
and actually attacked

08:31.760 --> 08:33.052
Somerset medical examiner
Thomas Maitland--

08:33.053 --> 08:35.763
- Horseshit.
- Shut up, Tony. It's on the fucking news.

08:35.764 --> 08:38.140
The news is always horseshit.

08:38.140 --> 08:40.768
Always make things sound worse
than they really are.

08:40.769 --> 08:43.895
That's how they sell soap.
The next morning, what happens?

08:43.897 --> 08:45.773
"Oh, sorry. Our mistake."

08:45.774 --> 08:48.484
I mean, seriously, who's gonna believe
this shit? Two dead people--

08:48.485 --> 08:51.487
Now five dead people.
And here's another.

08:51.488 --> 08:53.072
They're coming in from everywhere.

08:53.073 --> 08:56.784
A corpse at Hope Memorial
has apparently revived.

08:56.785 --> 08:58.744
That's six separate reports--

08:58.745 --> 09:00.996
Six? How could there be
six mistakes?

09:00.997 --> 09:03.832
For Christ's sake,
we hear this sort of thing every day.

09:03.833 --> 09:07.211
We got hurricanes
'cause the planet's getting too hot.

09:07.212 --> 09:09.213
And terrorists--
They're gonna drop a dirty bomb

09:09.214 --> 09:11.507
on the White House
or on your house.

09:11.508 --> 09:15.636
And somebody's gonna put some germ
in your water or in your mailbox.

09:15.637 --> 09:17.805
That letter from
Publishers Clearing House, huh?

09:17.806 --> 09:19.807
Good news is
you won a million bucks.

09:19.808 --> 09:22.726
Bad news is you're gonna
wake up dead tomorrow morning.

09:22.727 --> 09:24.311
Better believe what we've just heard.

09:24.312 --> 09:28.273
The problem doesn't seem to be
that people are waking up dead,

09:28.274 --> 09:30.234
but that dead people are waking up.

09:30.235 --> 09:32.778
Shh! Listen.

09:32.779 --> 09:35.364
- What's that?
- What was that?

09:35.365 --> 09:38.242
If this is some kind of Halloween prank

09:38.243 --> 09:40.202
or some sort of hoax,

09:40.203 --> 09:42.621
a lot of people are in on it,

09:42.622 --> 09:44.540
- including officials--
- I'm out of here.

09:44.541 --> 09:49.541
If I'm gonna wake up dead,
it's gonna be in my own bedroom.

09:49.838 --> 09:51.630
You can all come.

09:51.631 --> 09:53.966
Eliot has the address.
He knows where it is.

09:53.967 --> 09:55.884
Yeah. Nice place, too.

09:55.885 --> 09:58.554
Cozy. Takes up
about half of Philadelphia.

09:58.555 --> 10:00.013
Yeah, it's a fucking fortress.

10:00.014 --> 10:02.850
I can't get in unless I'm invited.

10:02.851 --> 10:04.810
Sorry, Jason, about your movie.

10:04.811 --> 10:06.812
I don't mean to hang
you up or anything,

10:06.813 --> 10:11.813
but I'm getting the fuck out of here.

10:13.695 --> 10:16.822
Like I said, you can all come.

10:16.823 --> 10:18.824
I mean it. It's an invitation.

10:18.825 --> 10:20.159
Late this afternoon,

10:20.160 --> 10:21.493
the cadaver began to move.

10:21.494 --> 10:23.871
- I'm in.
- Showed no vital signs,

10:23.872 --> 10:26.331
- but it opened its eyes--
- Anyone else?

10:26.332 --> 10:28.500
- Apparently not.
- How is that possible?

10:28.501 --> 10:30.169
The man must not have been dead.

10:30.170 --> 10:33.630
Not only dead. Partially dissected.

10:33.631 --> 10:38.631
BYE, guys.

10:38.887 --> 10:41.513
Fuckin' mummies get all the girls.

10:41.514 --> 10:44.767
So...what are we gonna do?

10:44.768 --> 10:46.769
The cadaver began to move.

10:46.770 --> 10:48.353
But how do you explain--

10:48.354 --> 10:50.272
As a medical man,
I have no explanation.

10:50.273 --> 10:51.899
I tell you what I'm gonna do.

10:51.900 --> 10:53.066
I'm gonna go to the dorm.

10:53.067 --> 10:55.819
Deb's there. Whatever's happening,
I don't want her to be alone.

10:55.820 --> 10:59.907
...able to transmit electrical impulses

10:59.908 --> 11:03.827
strong enough to animate
what little remained

11:03.828 --> 11:05.913
of the body's muscle and tissue.

11:10.919 --> 11:12.711
Okay,

11:12.712 --> 11:17.712
Okay, this is the women's dorm.

11:20.929 --> 11:23.931
Jesus!

11:23.932 --> 11:27.351
It's been 25 minutes
since we heard the news.

11:27.352 --> 11:32.352
It already looks
like everybody's gone.

11:38.947 --> 11:42.574
Hello. Who's in there?

11:42.575 --> 11:45.410
Oh, man.

11:45.411 --> 11:48.205
What the fuck are you doing here?

11:48.206 --> 11:51.458
- What the fuck are you doing here?
- I'm just stealing shit.

11:51.459 --> 11:53.335
But you--

11:53.336 --> 11:57.965
What's a guy with a video camera
doing in the women's dorm, huh?

11:57.966 --> 11:59.675
Security!

11:59.676 --> 12:02.427
Heh heh heh heh!

12:02.428 --> 12:04.555
Oh, man.

12:04.556 --> 12:06.974
Oh, God.

12:06.975 --> 12:11.975
Oh, shit.

12:15.984 --> 12:17.734
Okay. Okay.

12:17.735 --> 12:22.735
This is Deb's room.

12:23.283 --> 12:25.284
Oh, Jesus!
It's okay, Deb! It's me.

12:25.285 --> 12:27.995
Jesus-fucking...

12:27.996 --> 12:29.788
Are you still shooting?

12:29.789 --> 12:34.789
- Why are you shooting?
- I'm just--

12:34.961 --> 12:37.004
We have reports coming in from Denver.

12:37.005 --> 12:38.422
Oh, my God.

12:40.383 --> 12:43.802
- God, I'm so freaked.
- It's okay, babe.

12:43.803 --> 12:45.470
We have incredible footage
from Channel 10.

12:45.471 --> 12:47.222
I'm here. I'm here.

12:47.223 --> 12:51.059
I've been trying to call home
for, like, an hour.

12:51.060 --> 12:54.354
First exclusive footage that
shows evidence of dead people,

12:54.355 --> 12:58.191
or supposedly dead people, reviving.

13:00.028 --> 13:03.322
Jesus! What the fuck is that?

13:03.323 --> 13:05.324
Oh, my God.
The other one's coming up, too.

13:05.325 --> 13:07.993
' Shit! Shit!

13:07.994 --> 13:10.454
Same fucking thing!
No answer!

13:10.455 --> 13:13.081
- Gotta get out there. I'm missing everything.
- Babe.

13:13.082 --> 13:15.417
- What?
- There's no answer at my house.

13:15.418 --> 13:18.754
My morn, my dad, Billy--
They're supposed to be there.

13:18.755 --> 13:20.839
- Maybe they're up at the cabin.
- No, I already tried there.

13:20.840 --> 13:22.507
And their cell.

13:22.508 --> 13:24.051
He was walking really strange.

13:24.052 --> 13:25.427
Due to unusual volume,

13:25.428 --> 13:27.346
your call did not
go through as dialed.

13:27.347 --> 13:31.058
Circuits are busy. Your folks probably
can't get through to you, either.

13:31.059 --> 13:32.851
It was all over the news,

13:32.852 --> 13:34.645
all over the Web,

13:34.646 --> 13:36.897
but no one knew
what was really happening.

13:36.898 --> 13:39.524
I want to get out of here.

13:39.525 --> 13:43.445
Jay, I want to go home.

13:43.446 --> 13:46.031
He shot Ben!

13:46.032 --> 13:48.575
I think that's what started the panic--

13:48.576 --> 13:50.494
not knowing the truth.

13:50.495 --> 13:52.037
We're in a war zone,

13:52.038 --> 13:54.081
but I don't know who the war is with.

13:54.082 --> 13:56.208
What's been happening
is real, not a hoax,

13:56.209 --> 13:58.835
and prospects truly are terrifying.

13:58.836 --> 14:00.087
All my friends left

14:00.088 --> 14:01.630
before we could even say good-bye.

14:01.631 --> 14:04.007
- ...numbers of citizens--
- We want everyone to remain calm.

14:04.008 --> 14:07.469
It's funny. You spend so much time
resenting your parents,

14:07.470 --> 14:09.972
separating yourself,
building your own life.

14:09.973 --> 14:12.015
But as soon as
the shit hits the fan,

14:12.016 --> 14:17.016
the only place
you want to go is home.

14:19.232 --> 14:21.108
We're in Mary's Winnebago,

14:21.109 --> 14:22.401
trying to stick together.

14:22.402 --> 14:25.278
- What is this about, Jason?
- I don't know. I just--

14:25.279 --> 14:26.697
If this turns out to be a big thing,

14:26.698 --> 14:28.657
I just want to record it, okay?

14:28.658 --> 14:30.826
Come on. Everybody,
when it comes to you, say your name.

14:30.827 --> 14:35.455
This is ridiculous.

14:35.456 --> 14:37.749
Mary. Mary Dexter.

14:37.750 --> 14:39.501
And what are you doing here, Mary?

14:39.502 --> 14:41.336
Um, going home.

14:41.337 --> 14:44.297
Trying to go home.

14:44.298 --> 14:47.926
Can you just not film me while
I'm driving, please, so I can focus?

14:47.927 --> 14:49.136
- Say your name.
- Jason,

14:49.137 --> 14:50.637
if you don't know by name by now,

14:50.638 --> 14:52.389
then get your clothes
out of my closet, okay?

14:52.390 --> 14:57.390
- Come on, babe. It's part of history.
- His--

14:57.895 --> 14:59.896
Debra Moynahan.

14:59.897 --> 15:03.233
And I'm just trying to get home,
too, okay? Like Mary.

15:03.234 --> 15:08.234
And I'm wondering why my boyfriend
has a camera plastered to his face.

15:08.906 --> 15:10.782
Scranton, okay?

15:10.783 --> 15:14.077
Scranton, Pennsylvania.
That's my home.

15:14.078 --> 15:16.079
My parents' home.

15:16.080 --> 15:17.664
And my little brother's.

15:17.665 --> 15:19.666
Where are you coming from?

15:19.667 --> 15:21.460
College.

15:21.461 --> 15:23.879
We're all at Pitt together.

15:23.880 --> 15:25.797
University of Pittsburgh.

15:25.798 --> 15:28.216
- Why are we on the road?
- Christ.

15:28.217 --> 15:31.303
Yeah. Christ, Jason. Lay the fuck off.

15:31.304 --> 15:32.387
See this guy?

15:32.388 --> 15:35.724
He won't say who he is, so I will.
He's Tony Ravello, he's from--

15:35.725 --> 15:37.893
Where is it? Brooklyn? Or the Bronx?

15:37.894 --> 15:39.144
Queens.

15:39.145 --> 15:41.730
He does makeup that comes unglued.

15:41.731 --> 15:45.067
You know what?
I'm a directing major, just like you.

15:45.068 --> 15:46.693
I wasn't even supposed
to do makeup.

15:46.694 --> 15:48.904
No, I was.

15:48.905 --> 15:50.238
Sorry, babe.

15:50.239 --> 15:52.449
You know what happens
when we try to work together.

15:52.450 --> 15:57.450
I hear that.

15:58.164 --> 16:00.290
What are we doing
out here on the road?

16:00.291 --> 16:02.918
Uh, just trying to get
out of Dodge right now.

16:02.919 --> 16:04.836
Why?

16:04.837 --> 16:06.838
What do you want me to say, Jason?

16:06.839 --> 16:08.423
It's not what I want you to say.

16:08.424 --> 16:10.926
It's what you want to say. Tell us.

16:10.927 --> 16:13.428
Why does everyone want
to get the hell out of Dodge?

16:13.429 --> 16:14.930
'Cause of this thing--

16:14.931 --> 16:17.307
- this crazy thing that's happening.
- It is crazy.

16:17.308 --> 16:18.934
Where are you going, Tony?

16:18.935 --> 16:21.728
Nowhere. No place to go.

16:21.729 --> 16:25.398
So I'm just gonna hang with you, Jason,
until I can't take any more of your shit.

16:25.399 --> 16:26.733
- Got it.
- Will you explain

16:26.734 --> 16:28.318
why the Department
of Homeland Security

16:28.319 --> 16:31.738
suddenly raised its alert level
to orange earlier this evening,

16:31.739 --> 16:35.158
even though there are no indications
of a terrorist attack?

16:35.159 --> 16:36.827
You're right. There's no indication

16:36.828 --> 16:38.245
of any terrorism.

16:38.246 --> 16:41.998
We believe these are simply isolated
and unrelated phenomena,

16:41.999 --> 16:44.751
and we expect things
to return to normal very soon.

16:44.752 --> 16:46.962
See? Already starting to play the shit down.

16:46.963 --> 16:48.755
The Center for Disease Control
believes this may be due

16:48.756 --> 16:50.632
to a previously unknown viral strain

16:50.633 --> 16:53.760
that leads to a kind of mass psychosis.

16:53.761 --> 16:55.804
Psychosis.
Who's gonna believe that?

16:55.805 --> 16:57.764
- Psychotics.
- The president continues

16:57.765 --> 16:59.599
to monitor the situation from his ranch,

16:59.600 --> 17:02.144
and he's asked the American people
to remain vigilant.

17:03.396 --> 17:05.188
Say who you are, Eliot.

17:05.189 --> 17:06.772
You just did. I'm Eliot.

17:06.773 --> 17:08.191
Tell us more.

17:08.192 --> 17:10.609
Eliot Stone, Harrisburg, PA,

17:10.611 --> 17:14.781
and I'm here with you fine people because--
I don't know-- I'd like to get home, too.

17:14.781 --> 17:17.992
It's on the way. I'm hoping you'll be
so kind as to drop me off.

17:17.993 --> 17:20.287
Seems like everybody
wants to get home.

17:20.288 --> 17:22.204
I know what you're trying to do, Jason.

17:22.205 --> 17:23.790
I get it.

17:23.790 --> 17:26.792
Gordo Thorson, Danville, Pennsylvania.

17:26.794 --> 17:28.795
Tracy Thurman.

17:28.796 --> 17:31.214
We're, uh-- We're together.

17:31.215 --> 17:32.549
Forever.

17:32.550 --> 17:35.385
Uh, yeah. We'll see.

17:35.386 --> 17:36.803
What's that?

17:36.804 --> 17:38.013
Oh, this is my camera.

17:40.892 --> 17:42.309
Smile.

17:42.310 --> 17:44.561
Thurman and Thorson.

17:44.562 --> 17:46.771
Give me a kiss.

17:46.772 --> 17:48.690
Oh, and I'm from San Anton'.

17:48.691 --> 17:50.817
That's in Texas.

17:50.818 --> 17:52.402
Don't mess with Texas.

17:52.403 --> 17:54.738
Holy shit. Look at this guy.

17:54.739 --> 17:59.739
Christ.

18:00.036 --> 18:03.371
He's gotta be doing, like, a buck-20.

18:03.372 --> 18:04.789
Professor.

18:04.790 --> 18:06.791
Ah, you've finally come to me.

18:06.792 --> 18:09.211
I was beginning to feel neglected.

18:09.212 --> 18:10.420
It's just that you're--

18:10.421 --> 18:13.798
So far away, I know. In steerage.

18:13.799 --> 18:18.799
Sitting on a toilet seat
with everyone's dirty laundry.

18:19.055 --> 18:22.140
Oh, Andrew Maxwell, emeritus.

18:22.141 --> 18:27.141
Nowhere to go, nothing to do,
and I'm not with anybody.

18:28.105 --> 18:31.066
That was Ravello just
popping along for the ride.

18:31.067 --> 18:33.818
I'm not with anyone, either.

18:33.819 --> 18:36.154
I'm just here all alone.

18:36.155 --> 18:38.365
Just me and St. Chris.

18:38.366 --> 18:41.826
I think we'll be calling
on old St. Chris before this night's over.

18:41.827 --> 18:43.828
Oh, my God! Look!

18:43.829 --> 18:45.580
We'll never get past that.

18:45.581 --> 18:47.832
Turn around. We should
go back to the dorms.

18:47.833 --> 18:48.833
Look!

18:48.834 --> 18:50.293
It's a cop. A state trooper.

18:50.294 --> 18:51.711
How do you know that?

18:51.712 --> 18:53.713
Oh, his hat. His hat--
His stupid-looking hat.

18:53.714 --> 18:54.714
He looks hurt.

18:54.715 --> 18:56.716
- He's all burned up.
- Yeah.

18:56.717 --> 18:59.094
He's not just burned,
he's fucking fried!

18:59.095 --> 19:00.679
He shouldn't even be walking.

19:00.680 --> 19:02.347
- Oh, my--
- He's dead.

19:02.348 --> 19:03.390
God damn it!

19:03.391 --> 19:05.558
I'm telling you, he can't
be anything else but dead.

19:05.559 --> 19:08.103
- Oh, my God!
- Jesus fucking Christ!

19:08.104 --> 19:09.604
I think he wants more

19:09.605 --> 19:11.106
than your license and registration!

19:14.694 --> 19:19.694
- Go! Go--
- My God!

19:22.994 --> 19:24.202
Fuck!

19:24.203 --> 19:25.829
Wait. Before you go, wait, wait.

19:25.830 --> 19:29.958
What's that? What's that?

19:52.982 --> 19:54.482
What are we doing?

19:54.483 --> 19:55.775
What time is it'?

19:55.776 --> 19:57.402
It's almost 3.

19:57.403 --> 19:59.237
I think we should pull over.

20:09.206 --> 20:11.750
How do you feel?

20:11.751 --> 20:15.837
Mary, how do you feel
about what just happened?

20:15.838 --> 20:18.214
How do you think I feel?

20:18.215 --> 20:20.008
They were already dead, okay?

20:20.009 --> 20:22.344
You didn't do anything wrong.

20:22.345 --> 20:24.804
Listen to me, unless
you're Jesus fucking Christ,

20:24.805 --> 20:26.806
you don't stand up
and walk around after you're dead!

20:26.807 --> 20:28.767
Would you shut up?

20:28.768 --> 20:30.810
We might've just killed
three people back there.

20:30.811 --> 20:33.104
All right? Three living,
breathing people like us.

20:33.105 --> 20:37.817
No, we didn't.

20:37.818 --> 20:39.652
I did.

20:39.653 --> 20:44.653
I did.

20:44.992 --> 20:49.992
Sorry.

20:55.711 --> 21:00.711
Shit!

21:04.845 --> 21:09.845
We've stopped somewhere off the road.

21:10.393 --> 21:13.144
God knows where.

21:13.145 --> 21:15.480
Aren't you gonna go say something?

21:15.481 --> 21:20.481
I don't know, man.
I'll just give her some time, you know?

21:21.320 --> 21:23.738
I'm running low.

21:23.739 --> 21:28.159
I'd like to make it to a state store
before they all shut their doors forever.

21:28.160 --> 21:30.495
God, there's a terrible thought.

21:30.496 --> 21:33.540
A world where a gentleman
can't buy a bottle of bourbon.

21:35.334 --> 21:37.001
God.

21:37.002 --> 21:39.003
Mary? Mary?

21:39.004 --> 21:41.798
No! What did she do?

21:41.799 --> 21:43.800
What the fuck did she do?

21:43.801 --> 21:45.093
Anyone know she had a gun?

21:45.094 --> 21:46.636
Why would she do this?

21:46.637 --> 21:50.807
Because of what happened?
Those people back there?

21:50.808 --> 21:52.684
This is our fault.

21:52.685 --> 21:55.270
For panicking, for turning this into--

21:55.271 --> 21:56.896
Into what?

21:56.897 --> 21:58.982
Into something it's not.

21:58.983 --> 22:00.525
Into something more than this is.

22:00.526 --> 22:01.901
This is all just bullshit!

22:01.902 --> 22:03.111
You keep calling this bullshit,

22:03.112 --> 22:05.488
someone else is gonna kill themselves!

22:05.489 --> 22:07.157
You heard the TV.
Mary heard the TV.

22:07.158 --> 22:08.616
We all should've just stayed at school

22:08.617 --> 22:10.201
instead of driving around
in the middle of nowhere

22:10.202 --> 22:12.162
knocking fucking people off
like bowling pins!

22:12.163 --> 22:17.163
- She's still alive.
- What?

22:17.918 --> 22:19.836
She's got a pulse.

22:19.837 --> 22:23.965
- Fuck. Pressure. Pressure.
- Mary.

22:23.966 --> 22:26.509
- Looks like everyone's left.
- Yeah, left in a hurry.

22:26.510 --> 22:28.595
It's a hospital.
Where else is she supposed to go?

22:28.596 --> 22:30.930
Just because we can't see anybody
doesn't mean no one's here.

22:30.931 --> 22:31.931
Maybe they're hiding.

22:31.932 --> 22:33.808
Yeah, maybe they're hiding
'cause they think we're dead.

22:33.809 --> 22:35.101
Hello! We're not dead!

22:35.102 --> 22:37.896
Cut it out, Tony.

22:37.897 --> 22:39.898
Wait, wait, wait. Where are we going?

22:39.899 --> 22:43.401
You guys look for a doctor.
We're gonna find the E.R.

22:43.402 --> 22:46.779
Hello? Is anyone here?

22:46.780 --> 22:48.948
Wait, I think I hear somebody.

22:51.035 --> 22:56.035
It's down here. Come on.

23:02.087 --> 23:07.087
It's just the radio.

23:19.438 --> 23:22.440
We just saw some in the location...

23:22.441 --> 23:23.775
Hello?

23:23.776 --> 23:25.443
- Is anyone--
- Shh. Shh.

23:25.444 --> 23:26.444
What?

23:26.445 --> 23:28.071
...coming away from the building,
what's wrong?

23:28.072 --> 23:29.614
He wants to stay here

23:29.615 --> 23:31.449
'cause we can't move.

23:31.450 --> 23:33.117
Stand by. Stand by.

23:39.875 --> 23:42.460
It's complete chaos.

23:43.837 --> 23:45.755
It's complete fucking chaos.

23:45.756 --> 23:48.007
- We got him.
- I know I got him!

23:56.267 --> 23:57.767
Gotta go for the head.

23:57.768 --> 23:59.477
No, you gotta go for the head.

23:59.478 --> 24:03.481
Tell everyone out there
they've gotta get them in the head.

24:03.482 --> 24:07.485
This isn't some sort of mistake?

24:07.486 --> 24:12.448
This is a hospital. There's nobody here.

24:16.495 --> 24:20.290
What if it is for real?

24:20.291 --> 24:23.501
What about Mary?

24:23.502 --> 24:25.336
What if...

24:25.337 --> 24:26.879
she dies?

24:26.880 --> 24:28.506
We're not doing any good
just standing around here.

24:28.507 --> 24:30.300
Fuck. Losing juice.

24:30.301 --> 24:35.301
- Let's see if we can find some help.

24:36.724 --> 24:39.434
- There's somebody.
- Excuse me.

24:39.435 --> 24:41.227
Excuse me.

24:41.228 --> 24:42.353
We have an emergency.

24:42.354 --> 24:44.522
Our friend is hurt, and we need help.

24:45.524 --> 24:46.608
Oh, my God.

24:46.609 --> 24:48.026
What's wrong with him?

24:48.027 --> 24:49.569
He's dead,
that's what's wrong with him.

24:49.570 --> 24:50.653
Use the gun.

24:50.654 --> 24:51.821
- Oh, God.
- Hurry, use the gun.

24:51.822 --> 24:56.034
What if there's others?

24:56.035 --> 24:57.827
- Guys?
- Try the head.

24:57.828 --> 24:59.454
- Try the head.
- Yeah, shoot him in the head.

24:59.455 --> 25:02.874
Shoot him in the head!

25:02.875 --> 25:04.834
Fuck. Battery's almost dead.

25:04.835 --> 25:06.836
- Yeah, that's not all.
- What do you mean?

25:06.837 --> 25:07.879
What is going on?

25:07.880 --> 25:09.255
Jesus. A nurse.

25:09.256 --> 25:12.216
Dead doctor, dead nurse.
Makes sense, doesn't it?

25:13.302 --> 25:15.595
Let's fucking hurry up. Gordo!

25:15.596 --> 25:16.804
It's jammed.

25:16.805 --> 25:18.473
- Okay, I'm gonna try something.
- Try what?

25:18.474 --> 25:20.141
Get her attention.
Just try and get her attention.

25:20.142 --> 25:21.809
- Come over here.
- Hey!

25:21.810 --> 25:23.186
- Come after me.
- Be careful, Debra.

25:23.187 --> 25:24.270
Careful.

25:24.271 --> 25:25.647
Shock assigned.

25:25.648 --> 25:29.108
Jesus H...

25:29.109 --> 25:31.819
Christ.

25:31.820 --> 25:34.155
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Those are hot.

25:34.156 --> 25:36.824
Put them back where you found them.

25:38.994 --> 25:41.162
We got to get her a doctor.

25:41.163 --> 25:44.207
Yeah, a live one.

25:45.626 --> 25:50.626
I got it.

25:53.133 --> 25:54.133
Let's go.

25:57.388 --> 25:58.846
No, leave her here with me.

25:58.847 --> 26:00.098
What, you're not coming with us?

26:00.099 --> 26:01.516
I can't. I gotta plug in.

26:01.517 --> 26:03.059
Leave it. Let it charge.

26:03.060 --> 26:05.436
I can%.I can%leave
without the camera.

26:05.437 --> 26:06.896
The camera's the whole thing.

26:06.897 --> 26:08.272
Getting help is the whole thing.

26:18.033 --> 26:20.243
I should be with them.

26:20.244 --> 26:23.538
Maybe I could help.

26:23.539 --> 26:24.622
I can't.

26:24.623 --> 26:26.332
I can't...

26:26.333 --> 26:27.959
because...

26:27.960 --> 26:32.960
I'm fucking plugged in.

26:34.049 --> 26:36.551
Some shit, huh?

26:36.552 --> 26:41.552
Left alone with these fucking dead guys.

26:41.682 --> 26:43.558
I'm sorry, Mary.

26:43.559 --> 26:46.853
If anything Tony said or I said or did

26:46.854 --> 26:50.356
made you--

26:50.357 --> 26:52.900
People you killed were dead.

26:52.901 --> 26:55.570
These people are dead.

26:55.571 --> 26:58.865
At least they look dead.

26:58.866 --> 26:59.907
I don't know.

26:59.908 --> 27:03.828
The way things are...

27:03.829 --> 27:08.666
who the fuck knows?

27:08.667 --> 27:11.669
Mary.

27:11.670 --> 27:14.589
Mary?

27:17.593 --> 27:20.344
Shit.

27:21.597 --> 27:24.474
Guys?

27:25.601 --> 27:28.144
Guys, what's happening?

27:28.145 --> 27:29.645
Fuck. God damn it.

27:32.065 --> 27:35.443
Hello?

27:35.444 --> 27:38.738
Hello.

27:38.739 --> 27:43.739
I found this in one of the other rooms.

27:45.621 --> 27:47.079
Tell us your name.

27:47.080 --> 27:48.289
Uh...

27:48.290 --> 27:49.624
Say it.

27:49.625 --> 27:50.917
- Deb, come on.
- Say it.

27:50.918 --> 27:52.001
Give me a break.

27:52.002 --> 27:53.002
Jay-- Jason.

27:53.003 --> 27:55.296
- Jason Creed.
- You see how it feels

27:55.297 --> 27:57.757
to have a camera shoved in your face?

27:57.758 --> 28:00.718
To have to answer stupid questions
when people are dying all around you?

28:00.719 --> 28:02.094
You see how it feels?

28:02.095 --> 28:06.766
Deb, just put the thing down
and tell me what happened.

28:06.767 --> 28:09.101
Well, you missed it.

28:09.102 --> 28:14.102
If it didn't happen on camera,
it's like it didn't happen, right?

28:15.359 --> 28:16.651
There was a--

28:16.652 --> 28:20.112
There was a patient
in one of the other rooms.

28:20.113 --> 28:23.074
He looked nice, you know?

28:23.075 --> 28:25.034
Not dead.

28:25.035 --> 28:29.247
But he was.

28:29.248 --> 28:33.501
He was almost on top of me
before I saw him.

28:33.502 --> 28:38.502
It was Gordo who shot him.

28:38.507 --> 28:40.508
Jesus, did you--

28:40.509 --> 28:43.845
- I mean, did he--
- Hurt me?

28:43.846 --> 28:45.221
No.

28:45.222 --> 28:47.682
Well, who was screaming?

28:47.683 --> 28:49.016
Me.

28:49.017 --> 28:50.518
You want me to show you how?

28:50.519 --> 28:52.478
For the camera?

28:52.479 --> 28:54.522
For history?

28:54.523 --> 28:56.482
Aah!

28:56.483 --> 28:57.483
That's enough, Deb. I--

28:57.484 --> 28:59.819
Aah!

28:59.820 --> 29:04.820
Oh, God.

29:10.455 --> 29:15.126
I just shot another man.

29:15.127 --> 29:20.127
I've killed three men and a woman
in the last half hour.

29:20.340 --> 29:23.593
It came easily, too, didn't it?

29:23.594 --> 29:25.845
I remember the war.

29:25.846 --> 29:27.972
In wartime,

29:27.973 --> 29:30.558
killing comes easily,

29:30.559 --> 29:34.770
especially when you don't
have to do any of it.

29:34.771 --> 29:37.356
There will always be people like you,

29:37.357 --> 29:41.527
wanting to document,
wanting to record some sort of diary.

29:41.528 --> 29:43.863
Me? You're the one
who put the camera in my hands.

29:43.864 --> 29:45.907
You're the one
who made me want to do this.

29:45.908 --> 29:47.825
Not this. This is a diary of cruelty.

29:47.826 --> 29:49.994
And in wartime,
when the enemy can be marked

29:49.995 --> 29:52.830
as this son of a bitch
or that son of a bitch,

29:52.831 --> 29:55.166
then cruelty...

29:55.167 --> 29:57.084
becomes justified.

29:57.085 --> 29:59.754
Oh, my God.

29:59.755 --> 30:01.964
Oh, my God. Look at Mary.

30:01.965 --> 30:04.383
She's-- She's dead.

30:04.384 --> 30:07.470
She's turning.

30:08.889 --> 30:10.806
This is, like, too much.

30:10.807 --> 30:12.183
Too much.

30:13.518 --> 30:16.854
Guys, I don't know.

30:16.855 --> 30:18.522
Give it to me.

30:18.523 --> 30:23.523
You can't do this. Give me the gun.

30:32.079 --> 30:33.537
Oh, man.

30:33.538 --> 30:35.706
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

30:35.707 --> 30:39.543
You're stuttering, Mr. Creed.

30:39.544 --> 30:42.046
Don't try to speak, just shoot.

30:42.047 --> 30:45.633
Shoot your picture. Shoot for as long
as your hard drive holds out.

30:45.634 --> 30:49.428
As long as you have power.

30:49.429 --> 30:52.682
Take this.

30:52.683 --> 30:57.683
It's too easy to use.

30:59.856 --> 31:04.735
Let's get out of here.

31:04.736 --> 31:06.946
it's interesting how quickly we find out

31:06.947 --> 31:08.447
what we're capable of becoming.

31:11.827 --> 31:15.037
Up until that night,
we had lived predictable lives.

31:15.038 --> 31:16.330
Now...

31:16.331 --> 31:20.251
we would never be able to predict
what might happen next.

31:20.252 --> 31:22.712
God had changed the rules on us.

31:22.713 --> 31:27.713
And surprisingly, we were playing along.

31:31.555 --> 31:32.596
What the--

31:32.597 --> 31:35.141
Jesus, Gordo! Look out!

31:35.142 --> 31:36.600
Aah!

31:36.601 --> 31:41.601
What? What happened?

31:46.445 --> 31:48.112
You think they're not dead?
Huh, Tony?

31:48.113 --> 31:49.238
Tell me this guy isn't dead...

31:50.866 --> 31:53.576
...after I jam him
through the heart with a fucking I.V. pole!

31:53.577 --> 31:56.579
Jesus! Oh, regular fucking die, huh?

31:56.580 --> 32:01.580
You think he's not dead?

32:01.626 --> 32:03.085
DO you get it, Tony?

32:03.086 --> 32:08.086
Do you finally fucking understand?

32:14.639 --> 32:16.640
- What happened?
- It hurts.

32:16.641 --> 32:20.770
Bite.

32:20.771 --> 32:25.771
It hurts.

32:26.902 --> 32:28.903
Here, take this. It's too easy to use.

32:28.904 --> 32:31.197
Come on, Deb,
you used to shoot better than me.

32:31.198 --> 32:32.323
Yeah, that's why I stopped.

