40:48.570 --> 40:49.820
Come on.

40:49.821 --> 40:51.196
Come on, come on.

40:51.197 --> 40:54.908
Gentlemen, hurry.

40:54.909 --> 40:59.909
Aah!

41:03.209 --> 41:04.626
Oh, my God.

41:04.627 --> 41:06.336
- Oh, my God.
- It's all right. We're all right.

41:06.337 --> 41:07.963
There's nothing
we can do for him. Let's go.

41:07.964 --> 41:12.964
- But--
- They're gonna be all over us. Let's go!

41:25.356 --> 41:26.898
It's estimated that

41:26.899 --> 41:28.483
if something isn't done
to stop the slaughter

41:28.484 --> 41:31.903
within three more days,
our death rate will quadruple.

41:31.904 --> 41:34.239
Within 10 days,
it will have risen by 100%.

41:34.240 --> 41:35.699
Before there were--

41:35.700 --> 41:38.493
I don't know how many people
died every minute--

41:38.494 --> 41:41.705
8, 10, 20?

41:41.706 --> 41:44.708
Now there were five times
as many, ten times,

41:44.709 --> 41:47.919
a hundred times as many.

41:47.920 --> 41:51.715
Dead but walking.

41:51.716 --> 41:54.259
There weren't enough bullets
to stop them all.

41:54.260 --> 41:55.636
They are monsters.

41:55.637 --> 41:57.721
monsters who prey
on the flesh of the living.

41:57.722 --> 41:59.473
We needed supplies.

41:59.474 --> 42:00.766
Gas.

42:00.767 --> 42:03.393
Without gas,
we weren't going anywhere.

42:03.394 --> 42:04.728
There might be more of them around.

42:04.729 --> 42:05.854
Think we can make it?

42:05.855 --> 42:06.855
We've gotta try.

42:06.856 --> 42:08.940
Get in, fill up, get out fast.

42:08.941 --> 42:11.818
Yeah, but what if--

42:11.819 --> 42:14.071
- Put the gun down.
- Who the hell are you?

42:14.072 --> 42:16.990
Don't matter who I am.
All that matters is what I got.

42:16.991 --> 42:19.785
What he's got's
better than yours, Tony. Way better!

42:19.786 --> 42:22.829
Damn right. There here
is an M-16 semi-auto

42:22.830 --> 42:24.748
with the safety turned off.

42:24.749 --> 42:26.166
And I'm just trying to decide,

42:26.167 --> 42:27.751
do I pump two bullets into your brain

42:27.752 --> 42:30.045
or just one?

42:30.046 --> 42:34.675
No, we're cool.

42:34.676 --> 42:36.760
Good choice.

42:36.761 --> 42:38.804
Now who the hell are y'all?

42:38.805 --> 42:40.222
Some kind of newspeople?

42:40.223 --> 42:42.140
No. Students. University of Pittsburgh.

42:42.141 --> 42:46.144
Damn rowdies from town gone crazy.

42:46.145 --> 42:48.146
- Come on.
- Come on? Where?

42:48.147 --> 42:50.774
Anyplace is better than this, ain't it?

42:50.775 --> 42:55.775
Come on, before we get
our asses shot off!

42:56.781 --> 42:59.116
...always arguing about immigration.

42:59.117 --> 43:00.659
Let them in, keep them out,

43:00.660 --> 43:02.536
lock your door
and throw away the key.

43:02.537 --> 43:03.870
We've come here
concerned about people

43:03.871 --> 43:06.081
crossing the border into our country.

43:06.082 --> 43:07.791
But that's not the problem anymore.

43:07.792 --> 43:10.001
The problem
is all those creatures crossing the border

43:10.002 --> 43:15.002
between life and death.

43:16.259 --> 43:20.929
Ready for some boxes over there, man?

43:20.930 --> 43:23.223
What the hell's with
that camera anyway?

43:23.224 --> 43:25.225
Uh, home movies.

43:25.226 --> 43:30.226
Who's gonna be left to watch?

43:35.027 --> 43:36.862
So what's up with y'all?

43:36.863 --> 43:39.573
What the hell you doing in my town?

43:39.574 --> 43:42.743
We're trying to get to Scranton,
but we need fuel.

43:42.744 --> 43:44.703
We were using those pumps
back there at the gas station.

43:44.704 --> 43:46.288
Them pumps is dry.

43:46.289 --> 43:48.206
We siphoned off all the gas.

43:48.207 --> 43:50.709
- Can we buy some of what you took?
- Buy?

43:50.710 --> 43:53.712
Girl, if this keeps up,
money ain't gonna be worth nothing.

43:53.713 --> 43:56.006
Talking about gas, yeah,
I'll let you have some.

43:56.007 --> 43:57.924
Enough to get you where you're going.

43:57.925 --> 44:01.303
What's with you all?
How come you stuck around?

44:01.304 --> 44:03.597
'Cause we got the power.

44:03.598 --> 44:07.642
For the first time in our lives,
we got the power

44:07.643 --> 44:09.853
'cause everybody else left.

44:09.854 --> 44:12.189
All the folks without suntans.

44:12.190 --> 44:15.734
They'll be back, right?
The Army? National Guard?

44:15.735 --> 44:18.028
Somebody's gotta put
all this shit back together.

44:18.029 --> 44:19.946
The National Guard.

44:19.947 --> 44:21.907
Kid, I'm in the National Guard.

44:21.908 --> 44:24.868
Anyway, no one's
coming to put nothing together.

44:24.869 --> 44:26.870
That's why we got all this shit.

44:26.871 --> 44:28.789
Anything worth anything under one roof.

44:28.790 --> 44:30.248
- It's called looting.
- No, ma'am.

44:30.249 --> 44:33.794
It's called doing what you gotta do.

44:33.795 --> 44:35.962
Can I get online?

44:35.963 --> 44:38.757
Back there.

44:38.758 --> 44:41.635
Uh, excuse me.

44:41.636 --> 44:44.179
It's all right. Let him through.

44:44.180 --> 44:46.973
Let him through.

44:46.974 --> 44:48.350
In fact,

44:48.351 --> 44:51.853
law enforcement authorities
and a reporter was on the scene.

44:51.854 --> 44:54.773
Here's Homestead Chief
of Police Arthur Katz.

44:54.774 --> 44:57.776
These attacks was carried out
by a bunch of illegal immigrants

44:57.777 --> 45:01.655
was mistakenly pronounced dead
before the attacks took place.

45:01.656 --> 45:04.533
The only time they was dead
was when my guys shot 'em.

45:04.534 --> 45:07.285
They changed it. They recut it.

45:07.286 --> 45:09.871
The media were lying to us,

45:09.872 --> 45:12.040
or the government was lying to them.

45:12.041 --> 45:15.669
They were trying to make it seem
like everything was gonna be all right.

45:15.670 --> 45:16.711
What are you doing?

45:16.712 --> 45:19.047
I just want to shoot us
while we're editing.

45:19.048 --> 45:21.216
- Oh.
- I want to cover everything.

45:21.217 --> 45:22.759
Now I can understand

45:22.760 --> 45:25.679
why Jason was so anxious
to upload his own footage.

45:25.680 --> 45:29.057
- Okay.
- At the time, I didn't get it.

45:29.058 --> 45:33.478
Right there, we'll cut
to the angle from your camera.

45:33.479 --> 45:38.479
- Look!
- Perfect.

45:42.280 --> 45:44.823
- Put the gun down.
- Who the hell are you?

45:44.824 --> 45:47.993
Don't matter who I am.
All that matters is what I got.

45:47.994 --> 45:49.828
And after that, we drove here?

45:49.829 --> 45:51.830
Yeah. It sure would be nice

45:51.831 --> 45:53.164
to have the surveillance camera angle

45:53.165 --> 45:54.416
from when we drove in.

45:54.417 --> 45:57.419
Figured as much. Got it.

45:57.420 --> 45:59.504
They're recording all the security cameras.

45:59.505 --> 46:02.299
It's like a 7-Eleven in here.
I got it all cued up for you.

46:02.300 --> 46:04.843
- Oh, you're fucking brilliant, man.
- Why, thank you.

46:04.844 --> 46:06.511
What'd you do, get it off the recorders?

46:06.512 --> 46:08.179
It's a wireless system.
Pretty sophisticated.

46:08.180 --> 46:10.849
So sophisticated that I was
easily able to rip it off

46:10.850 --> 46:12.142
right out of the air.

46:12.143 --> 46:14.394
Beautiful. This is excellent.

46:14.395 --> 46:16.730
What the hell are you guys doing?

46:16.731 --> 46:19.482
Uh, editing.

46:19.483 --> 46:21.735
Editing what?

46:21.736 --> 46:23.653
The stuff we shot.

46:23.654 --> 46:25.739
When you said you want to get online,

46:25.740 --> 46:28.742
I thought you wanted to, like,
get in touch with your dad or something?

46:28.743 --> 46:30.952
No, I just wanted to upload our shit.

46:30.953 --> 46:35.457
Look, 72,000 hits...

46:35.458 --> 46:39.377
in eight minutes.

46:39.378 --> 46:41.421
Hey, Eliot, can we have a moment, please?

46:41.422 --> 46:46.422
Yeah.

46:46.928 --> 46:50.096
- ls his camera on?
