01:06:49.712 --> 01:06:51.588
You know, seems to be
a whole lot of folks

01:06:51.589 --> 01:06:56.589
getting a whole lot of stuff
from a whole lot of friends.

01:06:57.387 --> 01:07:01.431
Can we be friends?

01:07:01.432 --> 01:07:06.432
Want to turn that off, son?

01:07:06.563 --> 01:07:11.563
Turn it the fuck off.

01:07:11.568 --> 01:07:16.029
Now.

01:07:29.460 --> 01:07:34.460
There's your fucking
National Guard, Tony.

01:07:35.341 --> 01:07:36.550
They stole everything we got.

01:07:36.551 --> 01:07:38.802
Not everything.
They left us our weapons.

01:07:38.803 --> 01:07:40.012
Sure, but they have their own.

01:07:40.013 --> 01:07:42.639
They're military men.

01:07:42.640 --> 01:07:44.433
With the world being what it is,

01:07:44.434 --> 01:07:47.477
they knew we wouldn't
survive without weapons.

01:07:47.478 --> 01:07:50.063
They're not murderers, just thieves.

01:07:50.064 --> 01:07:52.649
The world being what it is.

01:07:52.650 --> 01:07:54.193
Think about that.

01:07:54.194 --> 01:07:56.278
From now on,

01:07:56.279 --> 01:07:58.488
everyone who dies...

01:07:58.489 --> 01:08:00.365
is gonna come back.

01:08:00.366 --> 01:08:02.951
I mean, think about that.

01:08:02.952 --> 01:08:04.912
Everyone who dies,

01:08:04.913 --> 01:08:06.747
unless they get a bullet in the head,

01:08:06.748 --> 01:08:10.334
is gonna come back
and try to kill somebody else.

01:08:10.335 --> 01:08:15.335
And on and on and on.

01:08:15.757 --> 01:08:20.756
Forever.

01:08:23.598 --> 01:08:24.640
Turn your helmet cams on.

01:08:26.309 --> 01:08:31.309
See anyone alive, pull them out.

01:08:31.439 --> 01:08:34.316
Hey! Anyone in there?

01:08:34.317 --> 01:08:36.401
Anybody home?

01:08:36.402 --> 01:08:37.736
- Wait. Hold it.
- Don't go in there!

01:08:37.737 --> 01:08:39.404
Do not open that door!

01:08:39.404 --> 01:08:40.529
Hold it! Hold it!

01:08:40.531 --> 01:08:42.323
Hey, are you all right, mister?

01:08:42.325 --> 01:08:43.325
- Don't!
- Are you all right?

01:08:43.326 --> 01:08:44.533
You can't go in there!

01:08:44.535 --> 01:08:46.536
What are you hiding in there, old man?

01:08:46.537 --> 01:08:51.537
No! No, please!

01:09:00.093 --> 01:09:02.551
There's nobody in here.
I don't see anything.

01:09:03.554 --> 01:09:07.808
Aah!

01:09:07.809 --> 01:09:09.559
Son of a bitch!

01:09:14.564 --> 01:09:19.564
Over there! Behind you!

01:09:25.033 --> 01:09:27.493
You fucking dick!

01:09:27.495 --> 01:09:28.662
No! No!

01:09:28.662 --> 01:09:30.831
Hiding these fucking dead
pieces of meat in here?

01:09:30.832 --> 01:09:33.417
- Look what happens! Look what happens!
- Please don't!

01:09:33.417 --> 01:09:34.584
- No!
- They were family.

01:09:34.585 --> 01:09:36.712
- Kill him.
- They were family!

01:09:36.712 --> 01:09:41.712
- Kill the prick!
- No, don't shoot.

01:09:44.679 --> 01:09:46.680
Don't shoot him in the head.

01:09:46.680 --> 01:09:48.682
Shoot him in the heart.

01:09:48.683 --> 01:09:53.683
Let him fucking wake up dead.

01:10:03.781 --> 01:10:08.781
It used to be us against us.

01:10:13.249 --> 01:10:15.709
Now it's us against them.

01:10:15.710 --> 01:10:16.710
He was right.

01:10:16.711 --> 01:10:19.671
Us against them.

01:10:19.672 --> 01:10:22.007
Except they...

01:10:22.008 --> 01:10:27.008
are us.

01:10:31.893 --> 01:10:34.269
I know it's around here someplace.

01:10:34.270 --> 01:10:35.645
Right here. Here.

01:10:35.646 --> 01:10:36.730
Here it is.

01:10:36.731 --> 01:10:41.731
Wake up, guys.
Guys, come on! Wake up!

01:10:42.737 --> 01:10:45.030
Oh, man. It's huge.

01:10:45.031 --> 01:10:47.282
It's like what God might have built

01:10:47.283 --> 01:10:48.784
if only He had the money.

01:10:52.580 --> 01:10:55.248
Ridley made this place
sound like a fortress.

01:10:55.249 --> 01:10:57.209
Um, I've never been to a fortress before,

01:10:57.210 --> 01:11:01.004
but don't they usually
keep the doors locked?

01:11:01.005 --> 01:11:02.756
I told you. He said everything was cool.

01:11:02.757 --> 01:11:07.757
Well, that was yesterday.

01:11:31.411 --> 01:11:33.787
Plenty of security.

01:11:33.788 --> 01:11:35.914
There's gotta be monitors
around here somewhere.

01:11:35.915 --> 01:11:38.500
Monitors don't do us any good
unless somebody's watching.

01:11:38.501 --> 01:11:42.421
Someone might be
watching us right now.

01:11:42.422 --> 01:11:45.507
Okay. Let's go in.

01:11:45.508 --> 01:11:48.844
Wait, wait. Go back. Step back.

01:11:48.845 --> 01:11:53.845
I want to cover everything.

01:11:57.311 --> 01:12:02.311
Okay. Ready. Come in!

01:12:08.948 --> 01:12:11.366
I can't do this anymore.

01:12:11.367 --> 01:12:13.577
Every time we walk in somewhere,
somebody dies.

01:12:13.578 --> 01:12:15.370
Or somebody's already dead.

01:12:15.371 --> 01:12:17.581
It's gonna be the same everywhere we go.

01:12:17.582 --> 01:12:22.582
Shut the door.

01:12:24.005 --> 01:12:26.965
Ridley?

01:12:26.966 --> 01:12:29.217
Ridley!

01:12:29.218 --> 01:12:30.469
Francine?

01:12:30.470 --> 01:12:35.470
Hello!

01:12:40.688 --> 01:12:45.688
Ridley?

01:12:56.078 --> 01:12:58.246
Well, this is where the party was.

01:12:58.247 --> 01:13:00.415
Good Lord.

01:13:00.416 --> 01:13:03.877
Treasures. Absolute treasures.

01:13:03.878 --> 01:13:06.004
A Tale of Two Cities.

01:13:06.005 --> 01:13:07.839
First edition.

01:13:07.840 --> 01:13:10.717
Do you have any idea what this is worth?

01:13:10.718 --> 01:13:12.344
It was the best of times,

01:13:12.345 --> 01:13:16.723
it was the worst of times.

01:13:17.725 --> 01:13:18.892
- Well.
- Ridley!

01:13:18.893 --> 01:13:20.435
You scared us half to death!

01:13:20.436 --> 01:13:22.729
You came. Oh, this is great.

01:13:22.730 --> 01:13:26.900
This is just so fucking great
to have all you guys here.

01:13:26.901 --> 01:13:28.485
How you doing, bro?

01:13:28.486 --> 01:13:30.487
- Where's Francine?
- Where are your parents?

01:13:30.488 --> 01:13:32.906
- Out back.
- Why was the front door open?

01:13:32.907 --> 01:13:34.783
Oh, was it?

01:13:34.784 --> 01:13:36.159
I was outside. Just came back in.

01:13:36.160 --> 01:13:37.494
Must not have shut it behind me.

01:13:37.495 --> 01:13:38.745
Stupid.

01:13:38.746 --> 01:13:40.705
Just stupid. You know me.

01:13:40.706 --> 01:13:41.748
I'm stupid.

01:13:41.749 --> 01:13:43.750
What's in there?

01:13:43.751 --> 01:13:46.461
- The panic room.
- Wow.

01:13:46.462 --> 01:13:48.630
What's going on?
Why were you in there?

01:13:48.631 --> 01:13:50.382
Just checking the generator, that's all.

01:13:50.383 --> 01:13:51.758
Everything's fine.

01:13:51.759 --> 01:13:53.677
Even better now that you're here.

01:13:53.678 --> 01:13:55.262
God!

01:13:55.263 --> 01:13:58.598
It is just so great
to have you guys here!

01:14:00.101 --> 01:14:01.643
You must be totally burned.

01:14:01.644 --> 01:14:02.769
What can I get for you?

01:14:02.770 --> 01:14:04.020
Something to eat? Drink?

01:14:04.021 --> 01:14:05.522
A cocktail would be lovely.

01:14:05.523 --> 01:14:07.774
Well, the bar is right over there.

01:14:07.775 --> 01:14:09.401
I'd like to get this damned corset off.

01:14:09.402 --> 01:14:11.403
Can you help me?

01:14:11.404 --> 01:14:13.446
You know what I'd like?

01:14:13.447 --> 01:14:15.991
A long, hot bath.

01:14:15.992 --> 01:14:18.201
Pick a bathroom. We've got six.

01:14:18.202 --> 01:14:19.786
Clean towels, soap, shampoo.

01:14:19.787 --> 01:14:21.580
Whatever you need. Whatever.

01:14:22.790 --> 01:14:25.500
So nobody's tried
to break in or anything?

01:14:25.501 --> 01:14:27.794
Nobody around to break in.

01:14:27.795 --> 01:14:29.921
We're pretty isolated out here.

01:14:29.922 --> 01:14:32.048
Country club's closer
than the next house,

01:14:32.049 --> 01:14:36.970
but not too many people
interested in golf or tennis these days.

01:14:36.971 --> 01:14:38.930
Where's your stuff?

01:14:38.931 --> 01:14:41.016
You must have brought
some stuff with you.

01:14:41.017 --> 01:14:42.809
Dirty clothes. Bags of them.

01:14:42.810 --> 01:14:44.978
Well, bring it in. Bring it all in.

01:14:44.979 --> 01:14:48.023
Something tells me you're
gonna be here for a while.

01:14:48.024 --> 01:14:49.774
I'll go to the Winnie.

01:14:49.775 --> 01:14:52.319
I'll come with you.
I'd like to grab that other camera.

01:14:52.320 --> 01:14:55.614
Yeah, 'cause one's never enough.

01:14:55.615 --> 01:14:57.115
Here, you take this one.

01:14:57.116 --> 01:14:59.200
No, no. I don't want
to make this kind of movie.

01:14:59.201 --> 01:15:01.119
I don't want to make
this kind of movie, either,

01:15:01.120 --> 01:15:03.204
but I can't change the script.

01:15:03.205 --> 01:15:04.623
Here. See if you can resist.

01:15:04.624 --> 01:15:06.249
I don't want to do this.

01:15:06.250 --> 01:15:07.876
Jason.

01:15:07.877 --> 01:15:09.544
Jason, I don't want to do this.

01:15:23.559 --> 01:15:28.559
My father shot a rabbit!

01:15:31.233 --> 01:15:36.233
I thought it was in here.

01:15:37.740 --> 01:15:38.948
Oh!

01:15:38.949 --> 01:15:40.492
Hmm. Tony.

01:15:40.493 --> 01:15:41.826
You're filming.

01:15:41.827 --> 01:15:45.163
I guess Jason was right.
You can't resist.

01:15:45.164 --> 01:15:48.667
I'm filming you, Ridley,
'cause you're acting a little weird.

01:15:48.668 --> 01:15:50.710
All this shit that's been going on.

01:15:50.711 --> 01:15:52.962
I know.

01:15:52.963 --> 01:15:55.674
I know what's going on.

01:15:55.675 --> 01:15:58.593
Still a little bit tired and--

01:15:58.594 --> 01:16:00.720
and a little drunk.

01:16:00.721 --> 01:16:02.847
That's all.

01:16:02.848 --> 01:16:03.973
Forget the rabbit.

01:16:03.974 --> 01:16:06.559
- Ridley?
- How about some pheasant?

01:16:06.560 --> 01:16:07.727
Father shot two of those.

01:16:07.728 --> 01:16:09.521
They're downstairs
in one of the big freezers.

01:16:09.522 --> 01:16:13.692
Ridley, can we go see Francine now?

01:16:13.693 --> 01:16:15.735
She's out back...

01:16:15.736 --> 01:16:18.446
with my family and the staff.

01:16:18.447 --> 01:16:19.864
Yeah, you said that.

01:16:19.865 --> 01:16:24.202
Why don't we go see her?

01:16:24.203 --> 01:16:26.538
I don't think we should do that.

01:16:26.539 --> 01:16:29.666
- Why?
- Well...

01:16:29.667 --> 01:16:31.626
to begin with...

01:16:31.627 --> 01:16:34.003
Father's dead.

01:16:34.004 --> 01:16:35.547
He was the first one to die.

01:16:35.548 --> 01:16:38.717
Then he did Mother,
and then they both did the staff.

01:16:38.718 --> 01:16:42.429
Brannigan, Brenda, Cook.

01:16:42.430 --> 01:16:44.681
Really liked Cook.

01:16:44.682 --> 01:16:46.725
Maybe she ate the rabbit.

01:16:46.726 --> 01:16:51.726
Did somebody eat Francine?

01:16:51.939 --> 01:16:54.941
Did somebody eat Francine?

01:16:54.942 --> 01:16:57.944
No.

01:16:57.945 --> 01:17:00.613
Well...

01:17:00.614 --> 01:17:02.449
no, not exactly.

01:17:02.450 --> 01:17:06.619
I mean, Brannigan bit her on her face.

01:17:06.620 --> 01:17:08.621
I think. I don't know.

01:17:08.622 --> 01:17:09.998
It all happened so fast.

01:17:09.999 --> 01:17:11.624
I think we should get out of here.

01:17:11.625 --> 01:17:12.709
Wait. Ridley?

01:17:12.710 --> 01:17:14.294
You're saying they're all dead.

01:17:14.295 --> 01:17:16.254
Yes.

01:17:16.255 --> 01:17:21.255
I had to bury them.

01:17:22.845 --> 01:17:27.515
Is no one else hungry?

01:17:27.516 --> 01:17:29.434
I didn't bury them in the garden.

01:17:29.435 --> 01:17:33.646
I'd never dig up Mother's roses.

01:17:33.647 --> 01:17:35.648
It's okay. Come on.

01:17:35.649 --> 01:17:37.984
I had to chop off Cook's hand.

01:17:37.985 --> 01:17:42.985
That's why there's so much blood.

01:17:43.282 --> 01:17:46.534
Shit.

01:17:46.535 --> 01:17:51.535
Come on.

01:17:54.668 --> 01:17:56.211
Maybe we should get out of here.

01:17:56.212 --> 01:17:58.838
No, I gotta see this.

01:17:58.839 --> 01:18:03.839
Guys.

01:18:16.857 --> 01:18:19.692
It's a little hard to see.

01:18:19.693 --> 01:18:24.693
Here, I'll turn on the lights.

01:18:26.033 --> 01:18:31.033
This is where I buried them.

01:18:34.708 --> 01:18:39.671
Sweet Jesus.

01:18:39.672 --> 01:18:42.882
- He's gone.
- There was blood on his arm.

01:18:42.883 --> 01:18:47.883
I wonder if he got bitten.

01:19:29.722 --> 01:19:34.722
Guys?

01:19:36.562 --> 01:19:41.562
Darlings?

01:20:04.089 --> 01:20:06.132
Jason, a little help here?

01:20:06.133 --> 01:20:11.133
I'm shooting.

01:20:11.597 --> 01:20:15.642
Oh, Ridley.
Can you give me a hand?

01:20:15.643 --> 01:20:17.810
- Aah!

01:20:17.811 --> 01:20:19.228
Jesus, he's dead.

01:20:19.229 --> 01:20:23.608
He's fucking dead.

01:20:23.609 --> 01:20:26.819
Oh, fuck.

01:20:26.820 --> 01:20:28.237
Jason!

01:20:28.238 --> 01:20:29.614
A little help here?

01:20:29.615 --> 01:20:30.615
Hey! Run!

01:20:30.616 --> 01:20:35.616
Run, Tracy!

01:20:39.708 --> 01:20:43.127
See? I told you
dead things move slow!

01:20:47.633 --> 01:20:52.633
Where the fuck did they go?

01:20:52.638 --> 01:20:56.182
Tracy? Tracy!

01:20:56.183 --> 01:20:58.977
Tracy!

01:20:58.978 --> 01:21:00.561
Oh, shit.

01:21:00.562 --> 01:21:02.063
I don't believe this.

01:21:02.064 --> 01:21:03.606
I don't fucking believe this!

01:21:03.607 --> 01:21:06.693
Just like your goddamn mummy movie!

01:21:06.694 --> 01:21:10.655
Jason, put down that
stupid camera and help me!

01:21:10.656 --> 01:21:11.990
Aah!

01:21:11.991 --> 01:21:15.952
Aah!

01:21:15.953 --> 01:21:17.245
You getting this, Jason?

01:21:17.246 --> 01:21:22.246
I hope you're happy, you son of a bitch!

01:21:24.003 --> 01:21:26.254
Hey! Hey!

01:21:26.255 --> 01:21:28.256
This isn't a movie, Jason. It's real!

01:21:28.257 --> 01:21:29.465
I'm trying to distract him.

01:21:29.466 --> 01:21:31.467
Cut! Cut!

01:21:31.468 --> 01:21:35.680
Cut!

01:21:38.684 --> 01:21:40.393
Don't mess with Texas.

01:21:51.280 --> 01:21:52.697
Tracy!

01:21:54.491 --> 01:21:56.617
Tracy!

01:21:56.618 --> 01:21:57.744
I'm leaving you, Jason.

01:21:57.745 --> 01:22:02.745
You can keep the house.
I'll take the car.

01:22:07.713 --> 01:22:09.172
Shit.

01:22:09.173 --> 01:22:10.590
I don't believe this.

01:22:10.591 --> 01:22:11.799
What is she, nuts?

01:22:11.800 --> 01:22:12.967
Where does she think she's going?

01:22:12.968 --> 01:22:17.968
She's not going for Chinese.

01:22:18.682 --> 01:22:19.891
You know what? It's okay.

01:22:19.892 --> 01:22:21.350
We-- We still got Ridley's car.

01:22:21.351 --> 01:22:22.769
There's other cars in the garage.

01:22:22.770 --> 01:22:24.604
- We could still get out of here.
- No, bad idea.

01:22:24.605 --> 01:22:27.523
Look, Ridley is still moping around
somewhere, dead or alive.

01:22:27.524 --> 01:22:31.027
And there are human goldfish
in the fucking pool.

01:22:31.028 --> 01:22:32.820
We just spent the last
two days on the road.

01:22:32.821 --> 01:22:34.822
- Did you have a good time?
- No, but--

01:22:34.823 --> 01:22:36.783
Out there, we're lunch.

01:22:36.784 --> 01:22:37.825
In here,

01:22:37.826 --> 01:22:39.577
there is a steel-reinforced panic room

01:22:39.578 --> 01:22:44.578
where could sit and play Nintendo
until this whole thing blows over.

01:23:09.650 --> 01:23:10.858
Shit!

01:23:10.859 --> 01:23:12.860
Don't, Deb! It's me.

01:23:12.861 --> 01:23:14.570
Jesus.

01:23:14.571 --> 01:23:15.988
Jesus.

01:23:15.989 --> 01:23:17.156
Where's Ridley?

01:23:17.157 --> 01:23:18.241
Have you seen him?

01:23:18.242 --> 01:23:21.202
Yeah, he's not Ridley anymore.

01:23:21.203 --> 01:23:23.204
He's something else.

01:23:23.205 --> 01:23:25.206
Eliot is something else, too, I'm afraid.

01:23:25.207 --> 01:23:26.541
What?

01:23:26.542 --> 01:23:29.752
Or gone.

01:23:29.753 --> 01:23:33.256
Died in a tub of water
with Ridley in his arms.

01:23:33.257 --> 01:23:35.591
- How do you know all this?
- I saw it on TV, darling.

01:23:35.592 --> 01:23:39.303
I took my bourbon, and I went in
to watch the monitors.

01:23:39.304 --> 01:23:40.680
I went into the panic room,

01:23:40.681 --> 01:23:45.681
which I suggest is a good place
for us all to go right now.

01:23:49.231 --> 01:23:52.984
Always fancied myself a swashbuckler.

01:23:52.985 --> 01:23:54.694
You're drunk, Professor.

01:23:54.695 --> 01:23:55.987
Indeed I am.

01:23:55.988 --> 01:23:59.657
But drunkenness has, oddly,
regretfully,

01:23:59.658 --> 01:24:03.161
never twisted my perceptions
of things going on around me.

01:24:03.162 --> 01:24:05.621
Tracy's phone. Let's go.

01:24:05.622 --> 01:24:07.832
- No.
- Jason.

01:24:07.833 --> 01:24:10.543
We can't just lock ourselves
in a fucking room.

01:24:10.544 --> 01:24:12.295
We'd be locking ourselves
out of the world.

01:24:12.296 --> 01:24:13.337
That's the whole point.

01:24:13.338 --> 01:24:16.549
We lock ourselves out of the world
before the world bites us on the ass.

01:24:16.550 --> 01:24:17.800
We've got weapons.

01:24:17.801 --> 01:24:20.678
We can take care of whatever comes.

01:24:20.679 --> 01:24:22.555
I can't go in there, Deb.

01:24:22.556 --> 01:24:24.307
I'll miss-- I'll miss everything.

01:24:24.308 --> 01:24:28.728
God damn it, Jason!
Would you stop this?

01:24:28.729 --> 01:24:30.396
Come with us.

01:24:30.397 --> 01:24:32.023
Be safe.

01:24:32.024 --> 01:24:33.733
Settle, like I'm trying to do.

01:24:33.734 --> 01:24:34.734
Settle for--

01:24:34.735 --> 01:24:36.652
- For what?
- For life.

01:24:36.653 --> 01:24:38.237
For survival.

01:24:38.238 --> 01:24:42.366
Survival? Who the fuck wants to survive
in a world like this?

01:24:42.367 --> 01:24:45.745
All that's left
is to record what's happening

01:24:45.746 --> 01:24:50.746
for whoever remains when it's over.

01:24:51.335 --> 01:24:54.879
Please.

01:24:54.880 --> 01:24:59.880
I don't want to go in there without you.

01:25:03.722 --> 01:25:08.722
All right.

01:25:18.820 --> 01:25:21.739
We can't.

01:25:30.999 --> 01:25:33.376
What was that?

01:25:33.377 --> 01:25:35.253
Where the hell is he?

01:25:38.882 --> 01:25:43.882
Oh, no.

01:25:44.137 --> 01:25:49.137
Oh, God.

01:25:49.643 --> 01:25:54.643
You fuck.

01:26:27.264 --> 01:26:32.264
Shoot me.

01:26:49.828 --> 01:26:51.203
Michael...

01:26:51.204 --> 01:26:56.204
the Archangel.

01:26:57.502 --> 01:26:59.879
Uh, ahem.

01:26:59.880 --> 01:27:03.257
Hi, my name is Jay-- Jason Creed,

01:27:03.258 --> 01:27:06.719
and I have been given
the opportunity--

01:27:06.720 --> 01:27:10.097
given the gift
to be able the document the events

01:27:10.098 --> 01:27:12.475
that have suddenly landed in my lap.

01:27:12.476 --> 01:27:14.268
And I just want to let you guys know--

01:27:14.269 --> 01:27:16.812
the audience know--
that I'm gonna do my best

01:27:16.813 --> 01:27:19.106
to capture the truth
with me and my friends.

01:27:19.107 --> 01:27:20.858
There's gonna be no fakeness.

01:27:20.859 --> 01:27:22.193
I'm gonna go after everything.

01:27:22.194 --> 01:27:23.861
Really raw, really real.

01:27:23.862 --> 01:27:27.615
And I'm going to do the best job I can.

01:27:27.616 --> 01:27:29.867
And I'm just really excited
to be given this opportunity.

01:27:29.868 --> 01:27:34.868
And I am not going to fuck it up.

01:27:35.582 --> 01:27:38.000
- Yeah.

01:27:38.001 --> 01:27:39.293
Debbie?

01:27:39.294 --> 01:27:42.838
Debra!

01:27:42.839 --> 01:27:47.839
Debra!

01:27:50.222 --> 01:27:55.222
Debra?

01:27:58.814 --> 01:28:02.691
Deb?

01:28:02.692 --> 01:28:07.692
I'm gonna finish his movie.

01:28:12.744 --> 01:28:14.995
The movie's over.

01:28:14.996 --> 01:28:18.124
No.

01:28:18.125 --> 01:28:21.961
There's gonna be more.

01:28:21.962 --> 01:28:24.088
There's gotta be more.

01:28:31.847 --> 01:28:34.473
Morning approaches.

01:28:34.474 --> 01:28:37.268
Things always look better
in the morning.

01:28:37.269 --> 01:28:39.270
Not to me.

01:28:39.271 --> 01:28:41.272
Mornings bring light.

01:28:41.273 --> 01:28:44.275
I prefer the darkness.

01:28:44.276 --> 01:28:47.153
It's easier to hide in the dark.

01:28:47.154 --> 01:28:48.988
You know what, Professor?

01:28:48.989 --> 01:28:52.283
I actually get the-- the mornings.

01:28:52.284 --> 01:28:56.787
They show you for what you are
instead of what you think you are.

01:28:57.789 --> 01:29:02.418
Inelegantly phrased, Mr. Ravello,
but accurately put.

01:29:02.419 --> 01:29:07.419
Mornings...and mirrors.

01:29:07.841 --> 01:29:10.759
I despise them.

01:29:10.760 --> 01:29:14.805
Mornings and mirrors
only serve to terrify old men.

01:29:14.806 --> 01:29:17.433
Hey, could you say that again?

01:29:17.434 --> 01:29:21.437
I didn't get that.

01:29:21.438 --> 01:29:22.438
Et tu, darling ?

01:29:22.439 --> 01:29:27.439
Look at this.

01:29:47.464 --> 01:29:52.464
Close the door.

01:29:57.349 --> 01:30:00.518
Jason once said he thought he could help,

01:30:00.519 --> 01:30:03.479
maybe even save some lives.

01:30:03.480 --> 01:30:07.608
This is the last thing
he downloaded before he died--

01:30:07.609 --> 01:30:10.778
a couple of hometown Joes
who went out to shoot at targets.

01:30:10.779 --> 01:30:13.614
But that day, they used people.

01:30:13.615 --> 01:30:15.533
Dead people.

01:30:15.534 --> 01:30:17.618
You know, just for fun?

01:30:19.204 --> 01:30:21.956
There was one target
that was different from the rest.

01:30:21.957 --> 01:30:23.457
A woman...

01:30:23.458 --> 01:30:26.627
tied by her hair to the branch of a tree.

01:30:26.628 --> 01:30:29.046
The boys had this one
set up just for kicks.

01:30:29.047 --> 01:30:29.880
The boys had this one
set up just for kicks.

01:30:29.881 --> 01:30:32.216
They got out their
favorite 12 gauge and--

01:30:36.388 --> 01:30:39.098
Are we worth saving?

01:30:39.099 --> 01:30:44.099
You tell me.
